      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OTHERONESON (4) has been contesting stronger races than this and looks well placed coming back to Provincial company. While he hasn't won for a long time, this presents as a golden opportunity with the figures he's produced in recent efforts. He maps to get his chance and he can end his winning drought. PRAY AGAIN (5) landed midfield and finished off well to just miss over the mile here 8 days ago. This is a tougher race, but he likes this track and trip and he drops 6kg. Can go one better today without surprising. WAYNE THE PAIN (7) was a winner over 1600m at Rockingham last time out, dropping out early before coming home with a powerful run to score by a neck. Will drift back but should be in the finish again. SKY GOD (6) showed good early dash and raced on the speed last start before fading to finish 8 lengths back in fifth over 1940m at this track. Cannot be underestimated. LITTLE SILVER (2) is next best.",
